The paper deals with learning user preferences over robot trajectories, which is a problem in robotics (cs.RO). The authors use machine learning techniques to learn the cost function that represents trajectory preferences, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). They also design a crowdsourcing system for collecting user feedback, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper involves learning from weak and noisy labels, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the experiments involve navigation and manipulation tasks in human environments, which could be related to computer vision (cs.CV).
